plans to launch a nuclearpowered spacecraft aboard the next space 
shuttle 
the spacecraft galileo waiting to be dispatched from atlantis on 
a sixyear voyage to jupiter will get its power from two nuclear 
generators containing 48 pounds of radioactive plutonium238 
the coalition has threatened to seek a court order and to 
trespass on the launch pad if necessary to stop the flight now set 
for oct 12 
nasa has released details of tests conducted on galileos radio 
isotope thermoelectric generators but the protest group is 
skeptical of space agency claims that there is virtually no chance 
of an explosion that would destroy the nuclear canisters and release 
lifethreatening radioactive fallout 
