scotland before coming here it wasnt worth the trip 
robbins an actor best known for the movie bull durham and 
simon have concocted an unfunny and heavyhanded comic strip 
masquerading as a play one of their main characters is a preacher 
named cotton slocum a rotund shaggyhaired charlatan who sells 
religion as if it were snake oil at a place called gods happy acre 
this is not a nonprofit organization slocum insists this is 
a church 
the minister and his carefully coiffured wife tipper are always 
in the market for new ways to make money he devises a prayer walk 
during which he will pound the pavement for the lord as well as for 
monetary pledges to finance his new religious theme park 
slocums assistant is a rightwing zombie named deacon tack who 
trains paramilitary cadets on the side the man combines the fervor 
of ollie north and the personality of bela lugosi 
mixed into this fanatic folderol is a sweet dimwitted housewife 
named dot who truly believes in slocum and her husband ralph who 
participates in tacks military maneuvers they all come together in 
